cilitate ion transport in\nsulfonated polysulfone membranes, without the need for long-range chain motion\nas in the case of traditional rubbery ionic polymers. Our estimates for the\ndielectric constant and b are used in conjunction with Manning's theory to\nestimate the fraction of counterions condensed to the fixed ions. The\nprediction of Manning's theory agrees well with the simulation result.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jan 2021 23:01:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-15"}
